</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="19" pageNumber="20" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1437,289,1141]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[201,336,901,925]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Etymology.</emphasis>
The generic name is derived from combination of two words 
<emphasis box="[1073,1135,902,925]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Purvi</emphasis>
+ 
<taxonomicName box="[1173,1252,901,925]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Agallia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1173,1252,901,925]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">agallia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the prefix is a Sanskrit word meaning early. The gender of the genus is feminine.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="19" pageNumber="20" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1437,289,1141]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[201,317,973,997]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[327,454,973,997]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Purvigallia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[327,454,973,997]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Purvigallia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
belongs to the group of genera with the hind margin of the head sinuate. It closely resembles 
<taxonomicName box="[270,418,1009,1033]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Japanagallia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[270,418,1009,1033]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Japanagallia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having a cross vein between the claval veins but is more robust and the ocelli are closer to each other than to adjacent eyes. It also resembles 
<taxonomicName box="[747,822,1046,1069]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Igerna" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[747,822,1046,1069]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Igerna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<emphasis box="[876,993,1045,1069]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Ianagallia</emphasis>
in external appearance but differs from 
<taxonomicName box="[151,226,1082,1105]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Igerna" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,226,1082,1105]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Igerna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having a pair of ventral processes on the aedeagus and from 
<emphasis box="[937,1054,1081,1105]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Ianagallia</emphasis>
in lacking a stout dorsal apodeme and having the aedeagal shaft stouter.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
